	<div itemprop="text"><p>Suppose I add a new custom field to my comment, say a boolean &#8220;Agree&#8221;. How could I query the comments of a particular post in order to get statistics on how many visitors agree with my blog post?</p>
</div>

	<div class="reply">
	<a class='comment-reply-link' href='/2010/wordpress-3-0-theme-tip-the-comment-form/comment-page-1/?replytocom=4569#respond' onclick='return addComment.moveForm("div-comment-4569", "4569", "respond", "137")'>Reply to this comment</a>	</div>
