	<div class="comment-meta commentmetadata"><a itemprop="url" href="http://ottopress.com/2010/wordpress-3-0-theme-tip-the-comment-form/comment-page-1/#comment-4666">
		<time itemprop="dateCreated" datetime="2010-08-24T10:41:24+00:00">August 24, 2010 at 10:41 am</time></a>	</div>

	<div itemprop="text"><p>Err&#8230; In fact, no, you can put any of that code into comments.php or into functions.php, depending on how you do it. Programming isn&#8217;t a matter of copy and pasting, you have to understand how the code works in order to know where to put it.</p>
<p>I tend to like to put things that modify the comments form at the top of the comments.php file of the theme, actually, because then it runs only when the comments form is actually going to be displayed.</p>
</div>

